<br>
&quot;Feel better, Persephone.&quot;<br>
<br>
::With that Hephaestus followed right behind Hades. The only thing that hollowed through the hall was the tapping of his crutch. He got on the chariot, and of course the entire chariot ride, did not ask any questions, merely thought to himself.::<br>
<br>
::When they got to Aetna, he stepped off and waved to his Uncle:: &quot;I'll try and help figure out how the Wards were depleted. In the meantime, I have to get back to work.&quot;<br>
