<br>
::He stepped off the chariot and tapped on the heads of both of the stallions. The moment he stepped out of the way the Chariot and the horses took off again, arriving back at the stables beside the palace. Of course some of the stable hands detached the chariot from the horses and let them back in. The chariot returned...with Hades::<br>
<br>
::Hades simply walked, he walked all the way to the River Styx. He stayed a distance away from where Charon, on his boat, was leading the souls across. He simply sat on the bank quietly, trying to calm down, because right now, even destroying a city the size of Athens and killing all of it inhabitants would not quench his anger. This was dangerous and he knew better, so he sat still trying to calm down.:: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=persephoneqofu>PersephoneQofU</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Silver Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 207<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(5/10/03 9:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=302.topic&index=69>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.aishwarya-rai.com/tradi/tash16.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> more to come</span><hr size=1> ::persephone sits in a chair awaiting Hades's arrival. Finally, she sighs and stands slowly::<br>
